title: For Sale:  Savage 93R 17HMR BTVS Rifle with extras (Scope, Case, Magazines)
postcontent:
I know how you feel. Tossing and turning every night, waking up in a cold sweat wondering, "AM I BRINGING ENOUGH GUN TO THE VARMINT BATTLE!?" 

Well, in 2002, the heavens were parted, and the .17 Hornady Magnum Rimfire cartridge was born. Developed by wildcatters and hailed by critics as the best ammunition innovation in 50 years, this cartridge has since served as the speed hungry, flat shooting, scary accurate cousin to its more humble rimfire relatives. 

"But..." you say, "isn't this cartridge too small to take down anything bigger than a squirrel!?" Let me stop you right there. It won't just take down a squirrel. Once the polymer tip cartridge contacts the squirrel, there is such a magnificent flurry of cartridge expansion and frangibility that the squirrel will cease to exist. Scientists call this radical change in matter disintegration, others call it ballistic magic.  People have taken down deer, coyotes, and bobcats with this screaming cartridge. A testament to skill, of course, but those legends were born out of using the right tool for the job. 

"But what about zombies???"

Son, just stop.

Included is Savage's homage to the mighty .17 HMR cartridge in the form of their flagship 93R17 rifle. This particular model, the BTVS, has a laminated wood thumbhole stock (looks like Michaelangelo scultped it himself during his tactical days), a floating barrel (likely designed by David Copperfield because it's a wonderous curiosity to behold), and slick stainless steel bolt hardware (Tony Stark probably was sought as a consultant for that portion).

In addition, it's only fair that this rifle have the right scope attached so you can see the perfectly round holes you'll be drilliing through quarters at 100 yards. Enter the Redfield Revolution 3-9x40 with Accu-Range Reticle. Forged by some of Leupold's best and brightest, you can watch the amazing fusion of science and physics play out in real time as your targets become history. High-mounted on custom ring mounts, this scope knows what's up.

title: For Sale:  Romanian ak-47 with Ammo and Extras
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Romanian AK-47. This is the Romak 991 model. It comes with gorgeous laminate wood thumbhole stock and forearm furniture. It is used and has some signs of use; however it is in great shape for its age. I have owned this rifle for a number of years and have enjoyed it the entire time, never had one issue with it. It is extremely dependable, lightweight, and easy to clean. The iron sights are dead on up to about 200 yards, and maybe further. I don't have anywhere to shoot further than 200 yards. I recently purchased a Sig Sauer 556r and it's time to find this AK a new home, although I hate to see it go. This rifle comes with the following:

- (2) 75 round high capacity drum magazines (these things are both fun and expensive)
 - Sturdy adjustable sling
 - Bump fire enabled trigger attachment (allows you to easily use the semi-auto recoil of the rifle to shoot in "full auto". Attachment can easily be removed, if desired)
 - 135 rounds of 7.63x39 ammo
 - Hard carry case (holds both the rifle and both drum magazines)
 - I have a regular (30 round???) magazine for this rifle somewhere. If I can find it, it's included as well.
 - Plenty of additional ammo available for purchase if needed.

Price - $800 OBO for everything. This is a steal; you will not be disappointed with this rifle and the drum magazines. I am not in a hurry to sell so lowball offers will be discarded. Will not separate, package deal only. Must be at least 18 yrs. old and have a valid Ohio ID to purchase, NO EXCEPTIONS!!! FTFsales only, no shipping. CCW owners preferred (like myself). Willing to meet in, or around, the Akron area. 

Although I'm not looking for any trades, feel free to try me. Will only consider high end optics and higher end 9mm semi-auto pistols for trade. Cash either way to make the trade fair.

title: For Sale:  Walther PPK late war party leader
postcontent: This is a late war party leader Walther PPK in 32 (7.65) caliber in very good condition with greater than 90 % of original bluing. Bluing is late war phosphate bluing. All guns made after mid-1943 were phosphate blued, so no high gloss finish as in early and pre war guns. Gun comes with original holster and two original magazines. Matching numbers on receiver, slide. Correct serial number range for party leader (between 173000k-411000k). Late war finish on wartime ppk’s were between 359000k-429000k. Correct markings for party leader throughout. Hoheitsabzeichen on grips and holster. Test proofs (Nitro) in correct locations (side of slide below ejection port, right side of chamber, and right side of barrel near muzzle). This is an authentic and original party leader grip with the machined metal clip inside the grip. The holster is not D.R.G.M marked, but is original to the gun. The bore is near mint on this gun as well as all internal parts. Party leader PPK’s were presented to NAZI party leaders. Approximately 4,000 party leader PPK’s with party leader grips and without RZM markings were made from 1935-1945. These guns are also rare because many were destroyed or discarded to help conceal identities of NAZI party leaders. The late war phosphate blued guns with black grip are partucularly rare
